          "In Grades K-8, students receive a strong foundation in economics. One-semester Economics for Grades 9-12 emphasizes economic decision making. Students will explore the interrelationships among consumers, producers, resources, and labor as well as the interrelationships between national and global economies. Additionally, students will examine the relationship between individual choices and the direct influence of these choices on occupational goals and future earning potential."
