        "date_valid": [
          "2008"
        ],
        "description": [
          "Instrumental Music I is a two-semester course designed to teach students music fundamentals and instrumental techniques pertaining to brass, woodwind, percussion, and/or string instruments. Instrumental Music I students are expected to develop beginning performance techniques in solo, small group, and large group settings, with emphasis on reading and performing using appropriate articulation, dynamics, and interpretive skills. Students will perform instrumental music in a variety of settings including, but not limited to, concerts, solo and ensemble performances, and festivals. Students will critique and reflect on their own performances and the performances of others. Students will make connections between music traditions and other arts, disciplines, and cultures. Students will apply rudiments of music and fundamentals of creative expression to performance and will demonstrate successful completion of Instrumental Music I student learning expectations."
        ],
