        "description": [
          "Language is the primary tool for communication in the rapidly shrinking, interdependent world of the twenty-first century. The ability to function competently in at least one language other than English has become increasingly important. One must be able to participate appropriately in face-to-face interaction with members of other societies. It is also necessary to interpret the concepts, ideas, and opinions of members of these societies, as expressed through their media and their literature. It is obvious that students only attain this ability when language study is initiated as early as possible and continued over an extended period of time. Futhermore, knowledge of the linguistic system of a given language—its grammar, vocabulary, and phonology-are important in supporting successful communication."
        ],
